[normal]The PEGI (Pan-European Game Information) system is a set of ethical standards in the format of a Code which reflect the industry’s commitment to 
[normal]act 
[normal]in a responsible manner towards children. The Code’s
[normal] main aim is to provide parents with objective, intelligible and reliable information regarding the minimum age for which a given product is deemed suitable, but the Code also deals with related advertising and promotion, consumer redress &amp; sanctions, comm
[normal]its members not to offend human decency and, after its merge with the PEGI Online Safety Code, now also aims to provide a safe online gaming environment for children.
